<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Why This Matters</p>
    <h2>Annual dryer vent cleaning is the single highest-leverage residential safety maintenance.</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>The U.S. Fire Administration estimates 2,900 home fires per year traced to clothes dryers. Lint accumulation in the vent line is the documented leading cause. The lint screen catches only about 75 to 80 percent of the lint produced — the rest travels through the vent and accumulates wherever the vent has bends, transitions, or restriction points.</p>
      <p>NFPA 211 (Standard for Chimneys, Fireplaces, Vents, and Solid Fuel Burning Appliances) recommends annual professional cleaning of residential dryer vents. Most LA homes we service have not been cleaned in 3 to 7 years — accumulation is significant and resolution is straightforward.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="alert-block">
      <div class="alert-label">&#128293; Annual cleaning prevents fire risk plus extends dryer life</div>
      <p>Restricted vent forces the dryer heating element to run longer per cycle, which accelerates element burnout (year 4-6 on neglected vents vs year 7-10 with regular cleaning). Annual cleaning at $140-$220 prevents both the fire risk and the $280-$440 heating element replacement cost.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
